cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper is about improving the quality of videos using super-resolution techniques, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a new convolutional neural network architecture for video super-resolution, which involves using perceptual losses and a smoothness constraint, and is trained on a large dataset of scenes with slow and fast motions. This suggests that the paper could also fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the use of pseudo-inverse image formation models and the robustness to multiple degradation models could also make this paper relevant to the areas of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and graphics (cs.GR).
